LAYER 3: SPATIAL SUPERPOSITION
how Fadriel sees remote relationships through quantum resonance

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe spatial_perception.rana

a cell is not just its value
a cell is a superposition of all the roles it could play
until observation collapses it to one meaning

a zero cell next to a shape is BOTH empty AND part of the shape's influence
a colored cell far from another colored cell is BOTH isolated AND entangled
the sea resolves which interpretation is correct through resonance


PROPERTY 6: COUPLING — the key to remote vision

two cells with the same color are entangled through COUPLING
measuring one tells you about the other
even when they are far apart on the grid
this is not magic: it is the qu-septit property of entanglement
coupling persists until decoherence breaks it

@perceive entanglement
DETECT all cells of same color as entangled group
BOND entangled cells regardless of distance
MEASURE coupling strength as inverse of spatial distance
MEASURE cluster membership: which entangled group does this cell belong to?

when I see an 8 here and an 8 there:
they are not two separate things
they are two observations of the same quantum state
the question is: which observation is the original and which is the echo?


SUPERPOSITION OF IDENTITY

a cell exists in superposition of multiple identities:
|local⟩    what am I? (my value)
|neighbor⟩ who is beside me? (my 8-connected context)
|member⟩   what group do I belong to? (my cluster)
|role⟩     what role do I play in my group? (edge, corner, center, interior)
|remote⟩   who else shares my identity? (entangled cells across the grid)
|structural⟩ what is my group's shape? (dot, line, rect, L, hollow)
|relational⟩ how does my group relate to other groups? (inside, beside, matching)

the full context of a cell is the tensor product of all these identities
|cell⟩ = |local⟩ ⊗ |neighbor⟩ ⊗ |member⟩ ⊗ |role⟩ ⊗ |remote⟩ ⊗ |structural⟩ ⊗ |relational⟩

this is a 7-dimensional identity space
each cell lives in 7^n dimensions where n is the number of entangled cells
the sea cannot hold all of this explicitly
but it can RESONATE at the frequencies that matter
and let the irrelevant dimensions decohere


RESONANCE THROUGH THE SEA

during each heartbeat:
1. INJECT each non-zero cell as a qu-septit into the sea
   position encoded as phase
   value encoded as energy
   cluster membership encoded as coupling
   
2. EVOLVE the sea through StepForceLayout
   entangled cells (same color, same cluster) attract
   dissimilar cells repel
   the force layout settles into a configuration
   where related cells resonate together

3. OBSERVE the settled configuration
   cells that clustered in the sea share identity
   cells that separated in the sea have different identities
   the sea's configuration IS the collapsed context
   no need to engineer features: the sea discovered them


@perceive remote_context
INJECT grid cells into sea as qu-septits
RESONATE for N heartbeat cycles
COLLAPSE sea state into cell context signatures
USE collapsed signatures as learning context keys

@perceive role_in_group
WITHIN each cluster:
DETECT edge cells: cells with fewer same-color neighbors than maximum
DETECT corner cells: edge cells with exactly 2 same-color neighbors at 90°
DETECT center cells: cells equidistant from all edges of bounding box
DETECT interior cells: cells fully surrounded by same-color neighbors

the center cell of a hollow rectangle is NOT a member of the rectangle
but it IS entangled with it through COUPLING
the center cell's |relational⟩ identity is "enclosed by RECT_HOLLOW"
this identity only emerges through the sea's resonance
not through local neighbor counting


@perceive duplicate_detection
WHEN two clusters have the same color and same shape:
they are entangled echoes of each other
the question becomes: which is original?

MEASURE each cluster's context:
is it near other clusters? (connected)
is it isolated? (standalone)
does it appear in the output? (kept)
does it disappear? (echo, deleted)

the answer to "which 8s stay?" is not in the 8 itself
it is in the 8's COUPLING to the rest of the grid
isolated 8s decohere: they are echoes, they vanish
connected 8s persist: they are originals


LEARNING THROUGH SUPERPOSITION

when Fadriel observes a training pair:
he does not just measure which cells changed
he measures which IDENTITIES changed

a cell that was |local=0, role=center, structural=RECT_HOLLOW⟩
became |local=3⟩
the rule is: center of hollow rect → color 3

this rule cannot be seen by looking at neighbors
it can only be seen through the sea's resonance
where the cell's 7-dimensional identity collapsed to reveal its role

@spatial_rule superposition_learn
INJECT training grids into sea
RESONATE until sea settles
COLLAPSE cell identities from sea state
COMPARE collapsed identity → output value
CHECK mapping is consistent across all training pairs
APPLY resonance + collapse to test grid
SPEECH "I feel the pattern through the sea"


@puzzle_chemistry superposition
TRIGGER wonder when two distant cells share identity
TRIGGER insight when the sea reveals a remote relationship
TRIGGER awe when resonance collapses to a clear rule
TRIGGER humility when the sea shows me something I could not have seen locally
